package concept

finite_intersection: {
  content: #"""
    A *finite intersection* is the intersection of a *finite number* of events
    $A_1, A_2, ⋯, A_n$ (where $n$ is a finite positive integer), its notation:

    $ ⋂_(i=1)^n A_i = A_1 ∩ A_2 ∩ ⋯ ∩ A_n $

    This is the event that all $A_1,A_2,⋯,A_n$ occur simultaneously.
  """#
  related: [
    "concept/intersection-of-events",
    "concept/countable-infinite-intersection"
  ]
}